people.name: Haute Wyatt
people.bio: Arrived at the Jamestown colony in late 1621 aboard the 	extit{George} and served as minister there for several years before returning to England.

people.name: George Wyatt
people.bio: Wrote a family history, published posthumously, under the title ``The papers of George Wyatt Esquire, of Boxley Abbey in the county of Kent, son and heir of Sir Thomas Wyatt the younger.''

people.name: Thomas Wyatt
people.bio: Led thousands of men in ``Wyatt's rebellion,'' an armed uprising in response to the announcement that England's Queen Mary I (``Bloody Mary'') would marry King Philip of Spain. Was soon captured, imprisoned at the Tower of London, and beheaded.

people.name: Thomas Wyatt
people.bio: A member of Parliament and an influential English poet; he was among the first writers to bring the sonnet to England. Was for a time imprisoned in the Tower of London on charges he committed adultery with Queen Anne Boleyn.

people.name: Thomas Brooke
people.title: 8th Baron Cobham
people.bio: Served in Parliament for several years, and fought at the Siege of Tournay in 1513.

people.name: John de Cobham
people.title: 2nd Baron Cobham
people.bio: Served in Parliament for several years.

people.name: Henry Wyatt
people.bio: A prominent English courtier, he served on the privy councils of kings Henry VII and Henry VIII. Made a knight of the Bath in 1509.

people.name: James Tuchet
people.title: 5th Baron Audley
people.bio: Fought in the Hundred Years' War, then became a prominent commander for the Lancasters in the Wars of the Roses; was killed at the Battle of Blore Heath, where ``Audley's Cross'' still stands, allegedly marking the spot where he died.

people.name: Joan de Geneville
people.title: 2nd Baroness Geneville
people.notes: in Volume I as 2,931, but we skipped her ancestors the first time through

people.name: Geoffrey de Geneville
people.title: Justiciar of Ireland
people.bio: Fought in the Eighth Crusade and served as chief governor of Ireland from 1273 to 1276.

people.name: Hugh de Lacy
people.bio: Participated in King Henry II's invasion of Ireland, after which he built multiple castles. Assassinated several years later by an Irish partisan.

people.name: Gilbert de Lacy
people.bio: Joined the Knights Templar in about 1158 and became a commander in conflicts around Jerusalem.

people.name: Roger de Lacy
people.bio: A Marcher Lord, one of the noblemen holding lands on the Welsh border.

people.name: Walter de Lacy
people.bio: A Norman nobleman who obtained lands in England after the Invasion of 1066. Died after falling off of scaffolding at a monastery.

people.name: Hugh XII of Lusignan
people.title: Count of Angouleme
people.bio: Killed fighting in the Eighth Crusade, 20 years after his father was killed fighting in the Seventh.

people.name: Hugh XI of Lusignan
people.bio: Killed fighting in Egypt in the Seventh Crusade, at the Battle of Fariskur.

people.name: Peter I
people.title: Duke of Brittany
people.bio: Fought in the Barons' Crusade of 1239; later died at sea during the Seventh Crusade.

people.name: Constance
people.title: Duchess of Brittany
people.bio: Featured as a character in ``King John,'' by William Shakespeare.

people.name: Odo of Rennes
people.title: Count of Penthievre
people.bio: Trained thousands of troops for the army of William the Conquerer in preparation for the Norman Invasion of 1066.

people.name: Geoffrey I
people.title: Duke of Brittany
people.bio: Died while on a pilgrimage to Rome.

people.name: Alain Canhiart
people.bio: His grave in Quimperle, in Brittany, was destroyed during the French Revolution.

people.name: Henry I
people.title: King of England
people.notes: Has a half-dozen daughters named Matilda or Maud, be careful

people.name: William des Roches
people.bio: Fought in the Third Crusade, including at the Siege of Acre and Battle of Jaffa.

people.name: Robert IV of Sable
people.bio: Served as grand master of the Knights Templar.

people.name: William de Ros
people.title: 6th Baron de Ros
people.bio: Named a Knight of the Garter in 1402.

people.name: Robert de Ros
people.bio: One of the 25 Magna Carta sureties.

people.name: William d'Aubigny
people.bio: One of the 25 sureties of the Magna Carta.

people.name: Ralph de Stafford
people.title: 1st Earl of Stafford
people.bio: Fought in the Hundred Years' War; named a Knight of the Garter.

people.name: Margaret de Audley
people.title: 2nd Baroness Audley
people.bio: Married Ralph Stafford after he kidnapped her.

people.name: Margaret de Clare
people.title: Countess of Gloucester
people.bio: Married Hugh de Audley at Windsor Castle.

people.name: John FitzAlan
people.title: 1st Baron Arundel
people.bio: Appointed Lord Marshal of England by King Richard II.

people.name: Roger de Quincy
people.title: 2nd Earl of Winchester
people.bio: Also served as the (hereditary) Constable of Scotland.

people.name: William Haute
people.bio: Fought at the Battle of Agincourt and later served in Parliament.

people.name: Richard Wydeville
people.title: Constable of the Tower of London

people.name: Richard Guildford
people.bio: Knight of the Garter. Died on a pilgrimage to Jerusalem.

people.name: William Finch
people.bio: Knighted after exemplary performance at the Battle of the Spurs in 1513.

people.name: Thomas Moyle
people.title: Speaker of the House of Commons

people.name: Edward Jordeyne
people.bio: A goldsmith who worked in the mint at the Tower of London.
